sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS AverageRating
FROM ratings
WHERE user_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- The "beacons of guidance" metaphorically refer to categories where the products receive the most helpful reviews. ;
- The "light of advice" refers to the 'helpful' field in the query, which indicates the helpfulness rating of reviews. ;
- The brightest "light" means the maximum value of 'helpful', implying the most helpful advice.

- Tree of knowledge refers to the hierarchical structure of categories;
- Branches represent individual categories within this structure;
- Roots are top-level categories with no parent;
- Leaves are the lowest-level categories without children;
- Depth in the tree indicates hierarchical levels.

sql:
SELECT email
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (
  SELECT reviewer_id 
  FROM reviews
)
AND user_id NOT IN (
  SELECT user_id 
  FROM ratings
);

SELECT products.title, reviews.sentiment
FROM products
JOIN reviews ON products.product_id = reviews.product_id;
